---
import DocsLayout from "../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout>
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-8 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-white">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="text-center mb-12 p-8 bg-linear-to-r from-purple-400/30 to-pink-500/30 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/20 backdrop-blur-sm">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <svg class="w-10 h-10 text-cyan-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19.428 15.428a2 2 0 00-1.022-.547l-2.387-.477a6 6 0 00-3.86.517l-.318.158a6 6 0 01-3.86.517L6.05 15.21a2 2 0 00-1.806.547M8 4h8l-1 1v5.172a2 2 0 00.586 1.414l5 5c1.26 1.26.367 3.414-1.415 3.414H4.828c-1.782 0-2.674-2.154-1.414-3.414l5-5A2 2 0 009 10.172V5L8 4z"/>
        </svg>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white bg-linear-to-r from-cyan-400 to-blue-400 bg-clip-text">
          Astro Islands
        </h1>
      </div>

      <p class="text-body/90 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Astro Islands (also known as Component Islands) is a revolutionary architecture pattern that allows you to build fast, interactive websites by hydrating only the components that need JavaScript.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-linear-to-r from-cyan-950/40 to-blue-950/40 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 p-4 rounded-lg">
        <p class="text-cyan-200 text-sm">
          üèùÔ∏è <strong>Core Concept:</strong> By default, Astro renders everything to HTML at build time with zero JavaScript. Islands let you selectively add interactivity only where needed, resulting in dramatically faster page loads.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What are Islands -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
        <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-cyan-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/>
        </svg>
        What are Astro Islands?
      </h2>

      <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default mb-6">
        <p class="text-body/80 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
          Think of your page as an ocean of static HTML. Islands are the interactive components that "float" on top:
        </p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
          <div class="bg-linear-to-br from-gray-950/50 to-slate-950/50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-500/20">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-400 mb-3">üåä The Ocean (Static)</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-body/80">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-gray-400">‚Üí</span>
                <span>Header, footer, navigation</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-gray-400">‚Üí</span>
                <span>Blog posts, articles</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-gray-400">‚Üí</span>
                <span>Images, text content</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-gray-400">‚Üí</span>
                <span><strong>Zero JavaScript shipped</strong></span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-linear-to-br from-cyan-950/50 to-blue-950/50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-cyan-500/20">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-400 mb-3">üèùÔ∏è The Islands (Interactive)</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-body/80">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-cyan-400">‚Üí</span>
                <span>Image carousels</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-cyan-400">‚Üí</span>
                <span>Search bars with autocomplete</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-cyan-400">‚Üí</span>
                <span>Shopping carts, forms</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-cyan-400">‚Üí</span>
                <span><strong>Only these load JavaScript</strong></span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-blue-950/30 border-l-4 border-blue-400 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <p class="text-blue-200 text-sm">
            üí° <strong>Key Benefit:</strong> A page with 10 components might only ship JavaScript for the 2 that actually need it. The other 8 are pure HTML/CSS.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How It Works -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
        <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-cyan-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10.325 4.317c.426-1.756 2.924-1.756 3.35 0a1.724 1.724 0 002.573 1.066c1.543-.94 3.31.826 2.37 2.37a1.724 1.724 0 001.065 2.572c1.756.426 1.756 2.924 0 3.35a1.724 1.724 0 00-1.066 2.573c.94 1.543-.826 3.31-2.37 2.37a1.724 1.724 0 00-2.572 1.065c-.426 1.756-2.924 1.756-3.35 0a1.724 1.724 0 00-2.573-1.066c-1.543.94-3.31-.826-2.37-2.37a1.724 1.724 0 00-1.065-2.572c-1.756-.426-1.756-2.924 0-3.35a1.724 1.724 0 001.066-2.573c-.94-1.543.826-3.31 2.37-2.37.996.608 2.296.07 2.572-1.065z"/>
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 12a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z"/>
        </svg>
        How It Works
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <!-- Step 1 -->
        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-linear-to-br from-cyan-500 to-blue-500 text-white font-bold text-lg rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">
              1
            </div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Server Renders Everything</h3>
              <p class="text-body/80">
                Astro renders all components to HTML on the server at build time. This includes both Astro components and framework components (React, Vue, etc.).
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 2 -->
        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-linear-to-br from-cyan-500 to-blue-500 text-white font-bold text-lg rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">
              2
            </div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Strips JavaScript by Default</h3>
              <p class="text-body/80">
                By default, Astro removes all JavaScript from framework components. They become static HTML.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 3 -->
        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-linear-to-br from-cyan-500 to-blue-500 text-white font-bold text-lg rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">
              3
            </div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2">You Choose What Hydrates</h3>
              <p class="text-body/80 mb-4">
                Use client directives to tell Astro which components need JavaScript and when to load it.
              </p>
              <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
                <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`---
import Counter from '../components/Counter.jsx';
import Carousel from '../components/Carousel.vue';
---

<!-- Static: No JavaScript -->
<Counter />

<!-- Island: Loads JavaScript immediately -->
<Counter client:load />

<!-- Island: Loads JavaScript when visible -->
<Carousel client:visible />`}</code></pre>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Client Directives -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
        <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-cyan-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"/>
        </svg>
        Client Directives
      </h2>

      <p class="text-body/80 mb-6">
        Client directives tell Astro <strong class="text-white">when</strong> to hydrate a component. Choose based on priority and user experience:
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <!-- client:load -->
        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default hover:border-cyan-500/50 transition-colors">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-3">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">client:load</h3>
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-red-500/20 text-red-300 text-xs rounded-full border border-red-500/30">High Priority</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-body/80 mb-3">
            Hydrates immediately on page load. Use for critical interactive components.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg mb-3">
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`<ShoppingCart client:load />`}</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm">
            <span class="text-yellow-400">‚ö†Ô∏è</span>
            <span class="text-body/70">Use sparingly - blocks page load</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- client:idle -->
        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default hover:border-cyan-500/50 transition-colors">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-3">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">client:idle</h3>
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-yellow-500/20 text-yellow-300 text-xs rounded-full border border-yellow-500/30">Medium Priority</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-body/80 mb-3">
            Hydrates when browser is idle (uses <code class="bg-black/30 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-cyan-300">requestIdleCallback</code>). Best for most interactive components.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg mb-3">
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`<SearchBar client:idle />
<Modal client:idle />`}</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm">
            <span class="text-green-400">‚úì</span>
            <span class="text-body/70">Recommended default for interactive components</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- client:visible -->
        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default hover:border-cyan-500/50 transition-colors">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-3">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">client:visible</h3>
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-green-500/20 text-green-300 text-xs rounded-full border border-green-500/30">Low Priority</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-body/80 mb-3">
            Hydrates when component enters viewport (uses <code class="bg-black/30 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-cyan-300">IntersectionObserver</code>). Perfect for below-the-fold content.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg mb-3">
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`<ImageCarousel client:visible />
<Comments client:visible />
<Footer client:visible />`}</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm">
            <span class="text-green-400">‚úì</span>
            <span class="text-body/70">Great for components below the fold</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- client:media -->
        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default hover:border-cyan-500/50 transition-colors">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-3">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">client:media</h3>
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-blue-500/20 text-blue-300 text-xs rounded-full border border-blue-500/30">Conditional</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-body/80 mb-3">
            Hydrates when media query matches. Useful for responsive components.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg mb-3">
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`<!-- Only hydrate on mobile -->
<MobileMenu client:media="(max-width: 768px)" />

<!-- Only hydrate on desktop -->
<DesktopSidebar client:media="(min-width: 1024px)" />`}</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm">
            <span class="text-green-400">‚úì</span>
            <span class="text-body/70">Perfect for mobile/desktop specific components</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- client:only -->
        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default hover:border-cyan-500/50 transition-colors">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-3">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">client:only</h3>
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-purple-500/20 text-purple-300 text-xs rounded-full border border-purple-500/30">Client-Only</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-body/80 mb-3">
            Skips server rendering entirely. Only renders on the client. Specify the framework.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg mb-3">
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`<!-- Components that can't render on server -->
<WebGLCanvas client:only="react" />
<BrowserAPI client:only="vue" />`}</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm">
            <span class="text-yellow-400">‚ö†Ô∏è</span>
            <span class="text-body/70">Use only when server rendering is impossible</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Framework Support -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
        <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-cyan-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 11H5m14 0a2 2 0 012 2v6a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2v-6a2 2 0 012-2m14 0V9a2 2 0 00-2-2M5 11V9a2 2 0 012-2m0 0V5a2 2 0 012-2h6a2 2 0 012 2v2M7 7h10"/>
        </svg>
        Framework Support
      </h2>

      <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default mb-6">
        <p class="text-body/80 mb-6">
          Astro Islands work with all major UI frameworks. You can even mix frameworks on the same page!
        </p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
          <div class="p-4 bg-black/30 rounded-lg border border-cyan-500/20">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-white mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="text-cyan-400">‚öõÔ∏è</span>
              React
            </h4>
            <code class="text-xs text-cyan-300">@astrojs/react</code>
          </div>

          <div class="p-4 bg-black/30 rounded-lg border border-green-500/20">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-white mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-400">üíö</span>
              Vue
            </h4>
            <code class="text-xs text-green-300">@astrojs/vue</code>
          </div>

          <div class="p-4 bg-black/30 rounded-lg border border-orange-500/20">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-white mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="text-orange-400">üî∂</span>
              Svelte
            </h4>
            <code class="text-xs text-orange-300">@astrojs/svelte</code>
          </div>

          <div class="p-4 bg-black/30 rounded-lg border border-blue-500/20">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-white mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="text-blue-400">‚ö°</span>
              Preact
            </h4>
            <code class="text-xs text-blue-300">@astrojs/preact</code>
          </div>

          <div class="p-4 bg-black/30 rounded-lg border border-red-500/20">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-white mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="text-red-400">üÖ∞Ô∏è</span>
              Solid
            </h4>
            <code class="text-xs text-red-300">@astrojs/solid-js</code>
          </div>

          <div class="p-4 bg-black/30 rounded-lg border border-purple-500/20">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-white mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="text-purple-400">üé®</span>
              Lit
            </h4>
            <code class="text-xs text-purple-300">@astrojs/lit</code>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Installation Example -->
      <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-cyan-500/30">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Adding a Framework</h3>
        <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`# Install React integration
npx astro add react

# Or manually
npm install @astrojs/react`}</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Practical Examples -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
        <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-cyan-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 20l4-16m4 4l4 4-4 4M6 16l-4-4 4-4"/>
        </svg>
        Practical Examples
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <!-- E-commerce Page -->
        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">E-commerce Product Page</h3>
          <p class="text-body/80 mb-4">
            Smart loading strategy for optimal performance:
          </p>
          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`---
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import ProductImages from '../components/ProductImages.jsx';
import AddToCart from '../components/AddToCart.jsx';
import Reviews from '../components/Reviews.jsx';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<!-- Static HTML - no JS -->
<Header />

<!-- Load immediately - critical functionality -->
<ProductImages client:load />
<AddToCart client:load />

<!-- Load when visible - below fold -->
<Reviews client:visible />

<!-- Static HTML - no JS -->
<Footer />`}</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Blog with Comments -->
        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Blog Post with Interactive Elements</h3>
          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`---
import BlogHeader from '../components/BlogHeader.astro';
import ShareButtons from '../components/ShareButtons.jsx';
import TableOfContents from '../components/TableOfContents.jsx';
import Comments from '../components/Comments.jsx';
import NewsletterSignup from '../components/NewsletterSignup.jsx';
---

<!-- Static - just HTML -->
<BlogHeader title={frontmatter.title} author={frontmatter.author} />

<!-- Hydrate when idle - low priority -->
<ShareButtons client:idle title={frontmatter.title} />
<TableOfContents client:idle headings={headings} />

<!-- Static content -->
<article>
  <slot />
</article>

<!-- Hydrate when visible - at bottom of page -->
<Comments client:visible postId={frontmatter.id} />
<NewsletterSignup client:visible />`}</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Responsive Navigation -->
        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Responsive Navigation</h3>
          <p class="text-body/80 mb-4">
            Different components for different screen sizes:
          </p>
          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`---
import DesktopNav from '../components/DesktopNav.astro';
import MobileMenu from '../components/MobileMenu.jsx';
---

<!-- Static on desktop -->
<DesktopNav />

<!-- Only hydrate on mobile devices -->
<MobileMenu client:media="(max-width: 768px)" />`}</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Performance Comparison -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
        <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-cyan-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"/>
        </svg>
        Performance Impact
      </h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <!-- Traditional SPA -->
        <div class="bg-red-950/20 border border-red-500/30 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-red-400 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span>üì¶</span>
            Traditional SPA (React/Vue)
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-body/80">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-red-400">‚Üí</span>
              <span>Ships <strong class="text-white">entire framework</strong> (~50-100KB)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-red-400">‚Üí</span>
              <span>Hydrates <strong class="text-white">all components</strong></span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-red-400">‚Üí</span>
              <span>JavaScript runs <strong class="text-white">before anything interactive</strong></span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-red-400">‚Üí</span>
              <span>Slower Time to Interactive (TTI)</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Astro Islands -->
        <div class="bg-green-950/20 border border-green-500/30 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-400 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span>üèùÔ∏è</span>
            Astro Islands
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-body/80">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-400">‚Üí</span>
              <span>Ships <strong class="text-white">only what you use</strong> (~5-20KB)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-400">‚Üí</span>
              <span>Hydrates <strong class="text-white">only interactive components</strong></span>
